This is an entertaining show. I normally don't like cop shows- I usually find them too repetitive and formulaic, but I tried this one because the price was so good. This show puts a strong focus on the characters and their relationships, which I like. Not every episode is just a 'case of the week' scenario. They make sure to have a continuous, evolving story line and keep things interesting. I especially like the relationship between Andy and Sam and how that develops. I recommend trying it even if you don't normally like cop shows and give it a few episodes- you'll be hooked. The quality of the picture on the DVD isn't perfect, no, but so what, the entire series is 30 dollars.  It's worth it.

I'm not reviewing the actual show, which is great and extremely enjoyable and the only reason for the 2 stars. Most of the other seasons of Rookie Blue were released on Blu-ray, and all were broadcast in HD. This SD DVD is however the only way to own this (and season 5, which is marked as Season 5 Part One but there is no part 2). This is one of the crappier dvd transfers I've ever seen. It's like they took the HD masters and stuck them on VHS then ripped the VHS' to DVD. Literally an hour of work max went into this. If you're a completest and fan of the show, obviously you'll need this, but don't expect it to be above VHS quality.

I watched several episodes and parts of others.  Finally had to give up.  What drivel.  Trade the uniforms for street clothes and move the characters over to the local high school and the picture would be complete.
Hissy fits, petty jealousies, juvenile spats, high school hijinks ad nauseam.  I was so embarrassed for the actors -- the script writing was so beneath their abilities.  Gag me with a spoon.
